cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CE 

This paper discusses the allocation of resources in ultra-dense small cell networks (SCNs) using a group buying mechanism. As such, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses coalition formation games (CFGs) and spectrum management, which are topics commonly found in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) category. The use of context awareness and decision-making algorithms falls under the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The paper also discusses load balancing and cooperative caching, which are topics commonly found in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) categories.
